    "title": "Line Graphs, Formulas, and Movies! Oh My!",
    "display_name": "Movies!",
    "long_instructions": "This data contains information about 2000 movies. Explore the data and answer the data questions:\r\n\r\n- How has the number of movies released annually changed over the past century?\r\n- Can we predict future trends in movie releases based on past data?\r\n- What does the trend behind the rate of movies released each year tell us?\r\n\r\n\r\n#####[Google Sheets Link](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1U2VPUTVPLVxHlmOr6FszAQ_FoNkLYxYnmnxjaoGfGtQ/)\r\n\r\nDo This\r\n#####1. Create a new collection based on the “year” and a new attribute showing the total of movies released yearly.\r\n\r\n<details><summary><strong>🔎 Expand me for help 🔎</strong></summary>\r\n\r\n- Drag the “year” attribute to the far left to create a new collection\r\n- Click the grey “+” icon to add a new attribute titled “Yearly Totals”\r\n- Click on the “Yearly Totals” attribute and select “Edit formula”\r\n- Add the “count()” function and click “Apply”\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n#####2. Add a graph to the workspace and the appropriate attributes that you think might be helpful to answer the three data questions above.\r\n\r\n\r\n<details><summary><strong>🔎 Expand me for help 🔎</strong></summary>\r\n\r\n- Add the “year” attribute to the x-axis. \r\n- Add the “Yearly Totals” attribute to the y-axis\r\n- Click on the “Measure” icon in the graph toolbar and select “Connecting Lines”\r\n- You should be able to answer all three questions using this line graph!\r\n</details>\r\n",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Can you add a formula to the data to create a line graph to answer questions about movies?",
